    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "9e2a5b34e90f18e594c928c303ed0b679107d3d6664d6e940786a715e27a2c7f",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "A problem of Erd\\H{o}s and S\\'{o}s. It is known (see [165]) that\\[R(3,k) \\asymp \\frac{k^2}{\\log k}.\\]The OpenAI bound of [1014] implies that\\[R(3,k+1)-R(3,k)\\ll k^{-c}R(3,k)\\]for some constant $c>0$. \n\nThis problem is #8 in Ramsey Theory in the graphs problem collection.\n\nSee also [165] and [1014]."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "db3a65fa8af21517d2bda2343dabf9e5be64d16881b47a7663d95bf45286862e",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Show that\\[R(3,k+1)-R(3,k)\\to\\infty\\]as $k\\to \\infty$. Similarly, prove or disprove that\\[R(3,k+1)-R(3,k)=o(k).\\]"
    }
  },
